Yep. You read me correctly.<br>
<br>
If I camp 40 or so hours for Casting Subtlety 3, then by george, I am goddam well getting it. I don't need kill placeholders for a rare spawn, or hope for a rare drop, or hope to win the random roll. I don't need my guild to go and kill something, and I don't need to worry about when the last time it spawned or whether another guild has gotten there first.<br>
<br>
When I got Spell Casting Mastery 3, I did not have to take off my velious quest shawl, with all its other stats, and trade it for an Obolus Death Shroud. When I got Quick Summoning 3, I did not have to take off my Prestidigitator's Crown and lost 30-odd some points of intelligence wearing a stupid Kobold Jester's Crown or whatever it is.<br>
<br>
When I attained Pet Discipline or Elemental Pact, it became a part of me, just like my spell book. There when I'm naked, at my bind point, there for a nasty CR wearing my banked gear and summoned items.<br>
<br>
Consider the hours spent farming AA compared to camping items or platinum, except I am camping platinum at the same time too.<br>
