Sure there are. Try reading the Magician Skills Forum for an idea of what skills people take for what reason, and how they use them. By and large I am very satisfied with my skills, including Regeneration, Running, Spell Casting Mastery, Spell Casting Fury, Spell Casting Subtlety, Quick Summoning, Elemental Pact, Pet Discipline, not to mention some odds and ends like a couple levels of Improved First Aid, which help me deal with all the dots I encounter solo. Magician class AA skills may not look like much on paper, but believe me, they make a lot of difference. Other mages have their favorites, read the forum and see!<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong. Gear is nice. I like gear. I like my right-clickies especially, and the extra intelligence, mana and hitpoints it brings. But gear doth not make the mage.<br>
